HEADWORD: Penned
<hw>Penned</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Winged;
having plumes.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Written with a pen; composed.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Their
<xex>penned</xex> speech.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Enclosed in a pen; -- of animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

